The evidence with the title 'Human development report 2014 ' says 3.8 by 2050 the share of people ages 60 and older in the world's population is expected to double to 15.5 percent , with the largest increase in East Asia and the Pacific . 69. 3.9 In Organisation For Economic Co-Operation And Development countries the poverty rate tends to be higher for older people than for the population . 
